-- Ministry Says Ukraine’s Winter Grain Sowing Increased by 8.5%
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-10-01T13:54:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/ministry-says-ukraine-s-winter-grain-sowing-increased-by-8-5-.html
Ukraine’s winter grain sowing
advanced 8.5 percent to 5.1 million hectares (12.6 million
acres) by today, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  Farmers had sown 4.7 million hectares by this time last
year, the Kiev-based ministry said in e-mailed statement today.
Winter wheat accounted for 4.6 million hectares, compared with
4.3 million hectares a year earlier, the ministry said. It said
8.2 million hectares will be sown with winter grains this year
for the 2013 harvest, the same as a year ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
